	<article id="post-1041" class="post-1041 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-centos category-linux category-ubuntu">
				<header class="entry-header">
			
						<h1 class="entry-title">
				<a href="http://codesleepshred.com/how-to-remove-crap-in-footer-php-w-grep-sed/" rel="bookmark">How To REMOVE Crap In footer.php w. grep sed</a>
			</h1>
										<div class="comments-link">
					<a href="http://codesleepshred.com/how-to-remove-crap-in-footer-php-w-grep-sed/#respond" title="Comment on How To REMOVE Crap In footer.php w. grep sed"><span class="leave-reply">Leave a reply</span></a>				</div><!-- .comments-link -->
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p><a href="http://www.brewdog.com/product/tactical-nuclear-penguin" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://codesleepshred.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/1//2013/01/penguin-beer.jpg" alt="penguin-beer" width="852" height="567" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1090" /></a></p>
<p>Lets get ride of garbage hard coded in premium themes. Only doing this because 1.) GPL and 2.) I paid for this theme, why is their copyright in it? <img src="http://codesleepshred.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" class="wp-smiley" />  Do I have to buy you a beer too? More than willing too. :]</p>
<pre class="brush: bash; title: ; notranslate" title="">grep -lr --include=footer.php &quot;&lt;p id=&quot;copyright&quot;&gt;&quot; /home/USERNAME/public_html/wp-content/themes | xargs sed -i 's#&lt;p id=&quot;copyright&quot;&gt;&lt;?php printf( __([^;]*; ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;##g'</pre>
<p>If this looks Greek to you, I&#8217;d recommend reading up on grep and sed documentation. There are great examples of how to use it with regex.</p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
